# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored; this example file is not.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      (bash)
#   copy .env.example .env    (cmd / PowerShell)
#
# Read ONLY by generate_eval.js, at build time, on your machine. The demo itself makes no
# network calls and needs no key -- do not add these to Vercel or any host's environment.
# Never rename with a NEXT_PUBLIC_ / VITE_ prefix: that inlines the value into the browser
# bundle and publishes your key.

# ---- required ----
LLM_API_KEY=

# ---- provider (defaults shown; uncomment to change) ----
# Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint works. Known free tiers:
#
#   Groq           https://api.groq.com/openai/v1                            openai/gpt-oss-120b
#   Cerebras       https://api.cerebras.ai/v1                                llama-3.3-70b
#   Mistral        https://api.mistral.ai/v1                                 mistral-small-latest
#   OpenRouter     https://openrouter.ai/api/v1                              <any model ending in :free>
#   Google Gemini  https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/  gemini-2.5-flash
#
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
# LLM_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-120b

# ---- throughput (defaults shown) ----
# Free tiers meter REQUESTS far more tightly than tokens. If you get a 429, read the
# provider's error text first: a quota cap needs FEWER requests (raise LLM_BATCH), a rate
# cap needs SLOWER ones (raise LLM_DELAY_MS). Measured 2026-07-15: Gemini's free tier
# allows 20 requests/day, so one-request-per-page could never have finished 41 pages.
#
# LLM_BATCH=8          # pages per request; 41 pages / 8 = 6 requests
# LLM_DELAY_MS=3000    # gap between requests
# LLM_CONCURRENCY=1    # requests in flight
